Vaal trainer Brett Webber was involved in a motor accident on his way to the racecourse yesterday morning around 5am when the bakkie in which he was driving overturned. Webber was taken to the Sebokeng Hospital but they were unable to admit him and he was later moved to the Mediclinic in Vereeniging. His condition is not known, however, he is believed to be conscious, despite having suffered some sort of head trauma. Would you like to place a bet on the horses? Click here to get started in 3 easy steps.